<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1083,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1192,1218]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">Head</emphasis>
. Antennomeres 28, bristly setose and 1.1× as long as fore wing; third segment 1.1× as long as fourth segment, length of third, fourth and penultimate segments 2.8, 2.5 and 1.5× their width, respectively (
<figureCitation box="[1235,1317,1227,1254]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1870,1895]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Bitomoides platyaulici, Sheng &amp; Chen, sp. n., ♀, holotype. 2—fore wing. 3—hind wing. 4a—mesosoma, lateral aspect. 4b—base of middle coxa. 5—mesosoma, dorsal aspect. 6—propodeum and first metasomal tergite, dorsal aspect. 7—antenna. 8—head, anterior aspect. 9—head, dorsal aspect. 10—head, lateral aspect. 11—hind leg and ovipositor, lateral aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839467/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); length of maxillary palp 0.6× height of head (
<figureCitation box="[556,638,1263,1290]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1870,1895]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Bitomoides platyaulici, Sheng &amp; Chen, sp. n., ♀, holotype. 2—fore wing. 3—hind wing. 4a—mesosoma, lateral aspect. 4b—base of middle coxa. 5—mesosoma, dorsal aspect. 6—propodeum and first metasomal tergite, dorsal aspect. 7—antenna. 8—head, anterior aspect. 9—head, dorsal aspect. 10—head, lateral aspect. 11—hind leg and ovipositor, lateral aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839467/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
); length of eye in dorsal view 4× temple (
<figureCitation box="[1109,1177,1263,1290]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1870,1895]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Bitomoides platyaulici, Sheng &amp; Chen, sp. n., ♀, holotype. 2—fore wing. 3—hind wing. 4a—mesosoma, lateral aspect. 4b—base of middle coxa. 5—mesosoma, dorsal aspect. 6—propodeum and first metasomal tergite, dorsal aspect. 7—antenna. 8—head, anterior aspect. 9—head, dorsal aspect. 10—head, lateral aspect. 11—hind leg and ovipositor, lateral aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839467/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); vertex punctate, with sparse setae and depressed near posterior ocelli; stemmaticum smooth; temple smooth and shiny, with sparse setae; OOL: diameter of ocellus: POL= 23:9:11; occipital carina absent dorsally, ventral part distinctly protruding dorsally and curved in middle level of eyes in lateral view; occipital carina far from hypostomal carina; hypostomal carina narrow (
<figureCitation box="[249,321,1407,1434]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1870,1895]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Bitomoides platyaulici, Sheng &amp; Chen, sp. n., ♀, holotype. 2—fore wing. 3—hind wing. 4a—mesosoma, lateral aspect. 4b—base of middle coxa. 5—mesosoma, dorsal aspect. 6—propodeum and first metasomal tergite, dorsal aspect. 7—antenna. 8—head, anterior aspect. 9—head, dorsal aspect. 10—head, lateral aspect. 11—hind leg and ovipositor, lateral aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839467/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
); face punctate and sparsely setose, without distinct middle carina(
<figureCitation box="[1105,1174,1407,1434]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1870,1895]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Bitomoides platyaulici, Sheng &amp; Chen, sp. n., ♀, holotype. 2—fore wing. 3—hind wing. 4a—mesosoma, lateral aspect. 4b—base of middle coxa. 5—mesosoma, dorsal aspect. 6—propodeum and first metasomal tergite, dorsal aspect. 7—antenna. 8—head, anterior aspect. 9—head, dorsal aspect. 10—head, lateral aspect. 11—hind leg and ovipositor, lateral aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839467/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); frons smooth behind antennal sockets; labrum glabrous and smooth, slightly depressed; clypeus transverse, flat, smooth and its ventral margin concave (
<figureCitation box="[343,410,1479,1506]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1870,1895]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Bitomoides platyaulici, Sheng &amp; Chen, sp. n., ♀, holotype. 2—fore wing. 3—hind wing. 4a—mesosoma, lateral aspect. 4b—base of middle coxa. 5—mesosoma, dorsal aspect. 6—propodeum and first metasomal tergite, dorsal aspect. 7—antenna. 8—head, anterior aspect. 9—head, dorsal aspect. 10—head, lateral aspect. 11—hind leg and ovipositor, lateral aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839467/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); width of clypeus 2.5× its maximum height and 0.5× width of face; hypoclypeal depression rather large and near triangular (
<figureCitation box="[523,593,1515,1542]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1870,1895]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Bitomoides platyaulici, Sheng &amp; Chen, sp. n., ♀, holotype. 2—fore wing. 3—hind wing. 4a—mesosoma, lateral aspect. 4b—base of middle coxa. 5—mesosoma, dorsal aspect. 6—propodeum and first metasomal tergite, dorsal aspect. 7—antenna. 8—head, anterior aspect. 9—head, dorsal aspect. 10—head, lateral aspect. 11—hind leg and ovipositor, lateral aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839467/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); mandible twisted, ventral carina nearly straight ventrally, gradually narrowed and with second teeth much smaller than first tooth (
<figureCitation box="[812,926,1551,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1870,1895]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Bitomoides platyaulici, Sheng &amp; Chen, sp. n., ♀, holotype. 2—fore wing. 3—hind wing. 4a—mesosoma, lateral aspect. 4b—base of middle coxa. 5—mesosoma, dorsal aspect. 6—propodeum and first metasomal tergite, dorsal aspect. 7—antenna. 8—head, anterior aspect. 9—head, dorsal aspect. 10—head, lateral aspect. 11—hind leg and ovipositor, lateral aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839467/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">Figs 2, 4a</figureCitation>
); a shallow furrow present in malar space and slightly sculptured ventrally, malar space remarkably longer than basal width of mandible.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1083,2010]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,152,252]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="590" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis box="[199,319,1624,1649]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. Length of mesosoma 1.3× its height; dorsal pronope absent; pronotal side largely smooth, but slightly crenulate anteriorly and posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[660,744,1659,1686]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1870,1895]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Bitomoides platyaulici, Sheng &amp; Chen, sp. n., ♀, holotype. 2—fore wing. 3—hind wing. 4a—mesosoma, lateral aspect. 4b—base of middle coxa. 5—mesosoma, dorsal aspect. 6—propodeum and first metasomal tergite, dorsal aspect. 7—antenna. 8—head, anterior aspect. 9—head, dorsal aspect. 10—head, lateral aspect. 11—hind leg and ovipositor, lateral aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839467/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
); propleuron flattened and slightly punctate; epicnemial area largely smooth, slightly crenulate; precoxal sulcus medium-sized, impressed, moderately crenulate and elongated to anterior margin of mesopleuron (
<figureCitation box="[556,639,1731,1758]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1870,1895]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Bitomoides platyaulici, Sheng &amp; Chen, sp. n., ♀, holotype. 2—fore wing. 3—hind wing. 4a—mesosoma, lateral aspect. 4b—base of middle coxa. 5—mesosoma, dorsal aspect. 6—propodeum and first metasomal tergite, dorsal aspect. 7—antenna. 8—head, anterior aspect. 9—head, dorsal aspect. 10—head, lateral aspect. 11—hind leg and ovipositor, lateral aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839467/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
); remainder of mesopleuron smooth and shiny, sparsely setose anterodorsally and postero-ventrally; pleural sulcus distinctly crenulate; mesosternum densely setose; mesosternal sulcus deep, medium-sized and crenulate; postpectal carina absent, but with circular carina at base of middle coxa distinct (
<figureCitation box="[160,243,1839,1866]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1870,1895]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Bitomoides platyaulici, Sheng &amp; Chen, sp. n., ♀, holotype. 2—fore wing. 3—hind wing. 4a—mesosoma, lateral aspect. 4b—base of middle coxa. 5—mesosoma, dorsal aspect. 6—propodeum and first metasomal tergite, dorsal aspect. 7—antenna. 8—head, anterior aspect. 9—head, dorsal aspect. 10—head, lateral aspect. 11—hind leg and ovipositor, lateral aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839467/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="589">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
); anterior groove of metapleuron largely smooth except a few crenulate ventrally; posterior groove of metapleuron densely crenulate, remainder of metapleuron smooth and shiny; mesoscutum quite shiny, finely punctate and with evenly setae; antero-lateral margin of mesoscutum densely sculptured and depressed deeply postero-laterally; notauli depressed anteriorly and absent on disc; medio-posterior depression of mesoscutum small, elliptical and present in a shallow longitudinal impression; scutellar sulcus deep and enlarged medially, with a distinct medio- longitudinal carina and several parallel-sided crenulate; scutellum flattened and smooth, (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1264,152,180]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1870,1895]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Bitomoides platyaulici, Sheng &amp; Chen, sp. n., ♀, holotype. 2—fore wing. 3—hind wing. 4a—mesosoma, lateral aspect. 4b—base of middle coxa. 5—mesosoma, dorsal aspect. 6—propodeum and first metasomal tergite, dorsal aspect. 7—antenna. 8—head, anterior aspect. 9—head, dorsal aspect. 10—head, lateral aspect. 11—hind leg and ovipositor, lateral aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839467/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="590">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
); lateral axillar lamella narrow; propodeum with a short medio-longitudinal carina and two oblique, transverse carinae, with several short longitudinal carinae posteriorly and remainder densely and coarsely reticulate-rugose (
<figureCitation box="[1184,1253,225,252]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1870,1895]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[222,1366,151,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Bitomoides platyaulici, Sheng &amp; Chen, sp. n., ♀, holotype. 2—fore wing. 3—hind wing. 4a—mesosoma, lateral aspect. 4b—base of middle coxa. 5—mesosoma, dorsal aspect. 6—propodeum and first metasomal tergite, dorsal aspect. 7—antenna. 8—head, anterior aspect. 9—head, dorsal aspect. 10—head, lateral aspect. 11—hind leg and ovipositor, lateral aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839467/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="590">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1117,1107,1132]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2839461/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="590" startId="2.[151,250,1107,1132]" targetBox="[282,1306,280,1048]" targetPageId="2">
