<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="592" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,153,179]" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">Etymology</emphasis>
. Name is derived from “platys” (Greek for “wide”) and “aulicis” (Greek for “furrow” or “groove”) because the scutellar sulcus is rather wide and enlarged medially.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="592" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,224,251]" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">Comments.</emphasis>
The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Papp, 1999" authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="1999" box="[688,1016,224,251]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Bitomoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latus">
<emphasis box="[688,878,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">Bitomoides latus</emphasis>
Papp, 1999
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wesmael, 1838)" authorityName="Wesmael" authorityYear="1838" baseAuthorityName="Wesmael" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[1075,1399,224,251]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Bitomoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosus">
<emphasis box="[1075,1197,225,250]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">B. rugosus</emphasis>
(Wesmael, 1838)
</taxonomicName>
by having the notauli only present anteriorly, medio-posterior depression of mesoscutum present (notauli largely impressed and medio-posterior depression of mesoscutum absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="1999" box="[883,1069,296,322]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Bitomoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latus">
<emphasis box="[883,1069,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">Bitomoides latus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wesmael" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[1123,1242,297,322]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Bitomoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosus">
<emphasis box="[1123,1242,297,322]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="592">B. rugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), scutellar sulcus enlarged medially with two large crenulations (scutellar sulcus rather narrow), M+CU1 of fore wing sclerotized (largely unsclerotized), r of fore wing 0.4× as long as 3-SR (0.14 times) (characteristics of the fore wing refers to those used in van Achterberg (2004)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
